dodTable.name: dodTable
dodTable.description: The DOD basic configuration table for each remote connection. All of the DOD tables are indexed (identified) by DestinationName.

dodTableID.name: dodTableID
dodTableID.description: The identifier number of this remote name. Each dod table will have a unique identifier number for it. The ID number is issued when the dod table of the destination name is created on the agent side. This object is obsoleted: use dodDestinationName as the index.

dodDestinationName.name: dodDestinationName
dodDestinationName.description: A textual description of the remote destination. The name is given by the manager side when the manager uses object dodTableOperation to create a new Dod record. The dodDestination is important. It will be used throughout all of the Dod database as index to access each object.

dodPassword.name: dodPassword
dodPassword.description: The password for this remote connection. It is used to check the remote's password when the remote client or server dials in. It is also used when authentication is enabled during outgoing calls. GENERR is returned if not authorized to read the dodPassword.

dodAuthenProtocol.name: dodAuthenProtocol
dodAuthenProtocol.description: The minimum authentication protocol this remote connection is using. It is one of CHAP or PAP or NONE. The actual authentication phase can be performed with a better protocol than specified here: for instance if set to PAP and the remote supports CHAP (as negotiated during the LCP phase), CHAP authentication will be performed. None means that authentication of this remote is disabled during outgoing calls. All incoming calls are ALWAYS authenticated, so setting this to none prevents from accepting incoming calls.

dodMaxLinks.name: dodMaxLinks
dodMaxLinks.description: The maximum number of links to be used when the system dials out or accepts incoming calls. Should be 1 or 2 for BRI lines.

dodBWThreshold.name: dodBWThreshold
dodBWThreshold.description: The threshold of bandwidth utilization of established links used to trigger an additional call, expressed as an integer percentage, i.e. 0 to 100. 0 means that all available links are dialed at once while 100 means that no additional links are used. The type of bandwidth measured by this object is defined by dodBODType.

dodTearDownTimer.name: dodTearDownTimer
dodTearDownTimer.description: The timeout limit to tear down the link when there is no activity for the link, expressed in seconds.

dodSourceIPAddress.name: dodSourceIPAddress
dodSourceIPAddress.description: The local IP address of the WAN port. It is used to negotiate with the remote side when dialing in or out. When nonzero, it overrides the default address, coming from the LAN port IP address (ethernet).

dodRemoteIPAddress.name: dodRemoteIPAddress
dodRemoteIPAddress.description: The remote IP address of the WAN port, if needed. Set to 0 otherwise.

dodSourceIPMask.name: dodSourceIPMask
dodSourceIPMask.description: The local IP net mask of the WAN port. It is used with dodSourceIPAddress.

dodRemoteIPMask.name: dodRemoteIPMask
dodRemoteIPMask.description: The remote side IP network mask.

dodIPXNetAddress.name: dodIPXNetAddress
dodIPXNetAddress.description: The IPX network address associated with the WAN link when connected to this remote.

dodIPFilters.name: dodIPFilters
dodIPFilters.description: Number of IP filters currently defined for this remote.

dodIPXFilters.name: dodIPXFilters
dodIPXFilters.description: Number of IPX filters currently defined for this remote

dodRemoteIPNets.name: dodRemoteIPNets
dodRemoteIPNets.description: This object describes the number of static IP routing entries for this destination name or connection. The static IP routing table is defined in another group.

dodRemoteIPXNets.name: dodRemoteIPXNets
dodRemoteIPXNets.description: This object describes the number of static IPX routing entries for this destination. The static IPX routing table is defined in another group.

dodRemoteIPXSAPs.name: dodRemoteIPXSAPs
dodRemoteIPXSAPs.description: This object describes the number of static IPX SAP entries for this destination. The static IPX SAP table is defined in another group.

dodRemoteMacState.name: dodRemoteMacState
dodRemoteMacState.description: This object controls the current bridge state (enabled or disabled) for this destination. When one of the remote destinations is turned on, the LAN port (ethernet) bridge capability will be turned on also, after a reboot. If this destination's bridge state is disabled and the bridge state of all the other destinations is also disabled, the LAN port bridge state will be disabled. Otherwise, if another destination's bridge state is still enabled, the LAN port bridge state will stay enabled. This mechanism is implemented in the system.

dodRemoteMacs.name: dodRemoteMacs
dodRemoteMacs.description: The number of specific MAC addresses defined to be statically bridged to this remote.

dodLastActivityTime.name: dodLastActivityTime
dodLastActivityTime.description: The last activity time with this destination

dodTableOperation.name: dodTableOperation
dodTableOperation.description: This object is used to create a new DOD record or to delete a DOD record.

dodMinLinks.name: dodMinLinks
dodMinLinks.description: The minimum number of links to be used when the system dials out or accepts incoming calls. Must be lower or equal to dodMaxLinks.

dodBODType.name: dodBODType
dodBODType.description: The type of traffic to which bandwidth measurement (defined by dodBWThreshold) applies.

dodIpOptRecvRIP.name: dodIpOptRecvRIP
dodIpOptRecvRIP.description: Allows processing of RIP packets received from this destination, when connected and IP routing is enabled in a RIP 1 compatible manner. dodIpOptRecvRIP, dodIpOptRecvRIP1, and dodIpOptRecvRIP2 are mutually exclusive.

dodIpOptSendRIP.name: dodIpOptSendRIP
dodIpOptSendRIP.description: Allows sending of RIP packets to this destination when connected and IP routing is enabled in a RIP 1 compatible manner. dodIpOptSendRIP, dodIpOptSendRIP1, and dodIpOptSendRIP2 are mutually exclusive.

dodIpOptRecvRIPDefault.name: dodIpOptRecvRIPDefault
dodIpOptRecvRIPDefault.description: Allows updating of the IP default route when receiving a RIP packet from this destination for the route 0.0.0.0.

dodIpOptSendRIPDefault.name: dodIpOptSendRIPDefault
dodIpOptSendRIPDefault.description: Allows sending of the IP default route (if known) to this destination when connected, as 0.0.0.0.

dodIpOptKeepPrivate.name: dodIpOptKeepPrivate
dodIpOptKeepPrivate.description: Allows to keep the route to this destination private, i.e. don't advertise it to other destinations

dodBrOptUseStp.name: dodBrOptUseStp
dodBrOptUseStp.description: Allows use of Bridging Spanning Tree Protocol when connected to this destination (causes a 40 second startup delay): use when topology loops are likely.

dodPPPOptUseLCPEcho.name: dodPPPOptUseLCPEcho
dodPPPOptUseLCPEcho.description: Perform a PPP LCP Echo request at regular intervals when connected to this destination.

dodEntryIsDisabled.name: dodEntryIsDisabled
dodEntryIsDisabled.description: This database entry is active (enabled) or temporarily disabled (i.e. bypassed when searching the database). This eliminates the need for constant add/removes.

dodCallbackOption.name: dodCallbackOption
dodCallbackOption.description: This option defines under what circumstances this system is allowed to dial the specified remote. The setting 'enable' means that this system is free to call the specified remote on its own and also to dial it back. Under the 'disable' setting, dialing back is never a possibility, but this system can dial the remote on its own if a phone number exists for it. The 'callback-only' setting prevents this system from calling the remote on its own: it will only perform the dial-back service. Note: in order to implement dial-back, Caller entries for this remote must exist (in dodCallerTable). This allows this system to identify what remote is calling, locating its database information and possibly calling it back. Caller Id verification (in fpSysCallerIdTable) is independent but uses the same dodCallerTable information.

dodSendDataAsVoice.name: dodSendDataAsVoice
dodSendDataAsVoice.description: This option determines whether ISDN data calls issued to this remote should be generated as voice calls instead of restricted or unrestricted digital (ISDN only).

dodIPXNetStrAddress.name: dodIPXNetStrAddress
dodIPXNetStrAddress.description: The IPX network address associated with the WAN link when connected to this remote. This is an alternative to the dodIPXNetAddress object to be used when OCTET STRINGs are not implemented. In this case, specify the IPX network number as an ASCII string containing from 1 to 8 characters, to be converted to hexadecimal by the firmware.

dodOurSystemName.name: dodOurSystemName
dodOurSystemName.description: Our system name (also called user name) when initiating a communication with this remote. It is used to override the global system name (fpSysName) and is useful when the name was assigned by the remote system admin, not by this system admin, in order to avoid using the same name (not under our control) for all connections.

dodOurPassword.name: dodOurPassword
dodOurPassword.description: Our system password when initiating a communication with this remote. It is used to override the global system password (when not empty) and is useful when the password was assigned by the remote system admin, not by this system admin, in order to avoid using the same password (not under our control) for all connections. GENERR is returned if not authorized to read the dodOurPassword.

dodPPPCallbackOption.name: dodPPPCallbackOption
dodPPPCallbackOption.description: This option defines under what circumstances this system is requesting a callback by using a method within the PPP protocol suite (as opposed to an ISDN callback). The possibilities are: - don't do any PPP callback (none) - ask the peer to us back based on the database record that he has for us (authentication). - supply the string (i.e. phone number, including prefixes etc,...) that the peer should use to call us back. - supply a location information which the peer will use in addition to our user name to call us back. - supply a E.164 string to the peer to call us back. - supply a generic string (name-string) to the peer so that it can use to it call us back using whatever method it deems appropriate. This router will force this to be the same as the remote name (index in the remote database) if it receives such a string.

dodPPPCallbackInfo.name: dodPPPCallbackInfo
dodPPPCallbackInfo.description: When the dodPPPCallbackOption is set to something other than none(1), this fields contains the additional information sent to the PPP peer when requested a callback.

dodDontAuthenticate.name: dodDontAuthenticate
dodDontAuthenticate.description: When enabled (1), do not request any authentication protocol when dialing out this destination. Note that an incoming call from this remote still requires some form of authentication (to find this remote entry record), as the key to the record is the authenticated name.

dodIPAddressTranslation.name: dodIPAddressTranslation
dodIPAddressTranslation.description: When enabled (1), do IP address translation for traffic to/from this remote.

dodIpOptRecvRIP1.name: dodIpOptRecvRIP1
dodIpOptRecvRIP1.description: Allows processing of RIP packets received from this destination, when connected and IP routing is enabled using RIP 1 only. dodIpOptRecvRIP, dodIpOptRecvRIP1, and dodIpOptRecvRIP2 are mutually exclusive.

dodIpOptSendRIP1.name: dodIpOptSendRIP1
dodIpOptSendRIP1.description: Allows sending of RIP packets to this destination when connected and IP routing is enabled using RIP 1 only. dodIpOptSendRIP, dodIpOptSendRIP1, and dodIpOptSendRIP2 are mutually exclusive.

dodIpOptRecvRIP2.name: dodIpOptRecvRIP2
dodIpOptRecvRIP2.description: Allows processing of RIP packets received from this destination, when connected and IP routing is enabled using RIP 2 only. dodIpOptRecvRIP, dodIpOptRecvRIP1, and dodIpOptRecvRIP2 are mutually exclusive.

dodIpOptSendRIP2.name: dodIpOptSendRIP2
dodIpOptSendRIP2.description: Allows sending of RIP packets to this destination when connected and IP routing is enabled using RIP 2 only. dodIpOptSendRIP, dodIpOptSendRIP1, and dodIpOptSendRIP2 are mutually exclusive.

dodProtocol.name: dodProtocol
dodProtocol.description: Type of protocol used for communicating with this remote.

dodCompression.name: dodCompression
dodCompression.description: When enabled (1), do compression for traffic to/from this remote.

dodPasswordSpecified.name: dodPasswordSpecified
dodPasswordSpecified.description: Return true if the password for this remote connection has been specified.

dodOurPasswordSpecified.name: dodOurPasswordSpecified
dodOurPasswordSpecified.description: Return true if our system password for this remote connnection has been specified.

dodBlockNetBIOS.name: dodBlockNetBIOS
dodBlockNetBIOS.description: When enabled (1), block NetBIOS traffic to this remote.

dodMtu.name: dodMtu
dodMtu.description: When non-zero, the desired MTU size for this remote. When zero, use the default MTU size for the interface. The MTU size used is the minimum of the desired MTU size for this remote and the maximum MTU size allowed for the interface.

dodIpSlaveMode.name: dodIpSlaveMode
dodIpSlaveMode.description: When enabled (1), always accept peer proposal for our IP address for our WAN interface.

dodReacquireIpAddr.name: dodReacquireIpAddr
dodReacquireIpAddr.description: When enabled (1), try to reacquire the last used IP address for this interface IF we believe any TCP connections are still active to this remote.

dodIpxOptRIPSAP.name: dodIpxOptRIPSAP
dodIpxOptRIPSAP.description: When enabled (1), allows IPXCP to negotiate the use of RIP and SAP IPX traffic. Actual use of the RIP and SAP protocols will depend on the capabilities of the remote at the time the PPP connection is established.

dodCallIDTable.name: dodCallIDTable
dodCallIDTable.description: A list of Call identifiers (phone number, DLCI ....) for a particular destination name and link type (ISDN). This table includes only two entries, type and phone number count.

dodCallIDEntry.name: dodCallIDEntry
dodCallIDEntry.description: An entry of Call identifier for each connection type.

dodCallIDPhones.name: dodCallIDPhones
dodCallIDPhones.description: Number of entries in the dodPhoneTable for this type of connection and this remote.

dodPhoneIndex.name: dodPhoneIndex
dodPhoneIndex.description: It is an index to recognize which phone number is in the table with the specified CallIDType and DestinationName.

dodPhoneSpeed.name: dodPhoneSpeed
dodPhoneSpeed.description: The line speed (in bits per seconds) for asynchronous connections.

dodRemoteMacTable.name: dodRemoteMacTable
dodRemoteMacTable.description: A table of MAC addresses for bridging of the specified destination name. The table is indexed by destination name and MAC address.

dodRemoteMacIndex.name: dodRemoteMacIndex
dodRemoteMacIndex.description: The index number is not used currently. User don't need to implement it currently. The table is indexed by the MAC address.

dodRemoteMacAddress.name: dodRemoteMacAddress
dodRemoteMacAddress.description: Contains the IEEE unique MAC address of statically configured devices for bridging purposes. When all of the 6 bytes of this MAC address are zero, the entry is called the unknown address. Any packet with a destination address not in the static or dynamic MAC table of any remote bridge will be sent to the default remote bridge (which has a dodRemoteMacAddress entry defined for the unknown MAC address).. There can be only one remote destination specified as default bridge, i.e. containing the unknown MAC address.

dodRemoteMacOperation.name: dodRemoteMacOperation
dodRemoteMacOperation.description: add -- add a static MAC address to be bridge to this remote destination. remove -- remove a static MAC address.

dodRemoteIPNetTable.name: dodRemoteIPNetTable
dodRemoteIPNetTable.description: The static IP routing table. It is based on indexes of destination name and IP net address.

dodRemoteIPNetIndex.name: dodRemoteIPNetIndex
dodRemoteIPNetIndex.description: This index is not currently in use.

dodRemoteIPNetAddress.name: dodRemoteIPNetAddress
dodRemoteIPNetAddress.description: The IP network address of an entry of the static IP routing table.

dodRemoteIPNetMask.name: dodRemoteIPNetMask
dodRemoteIPNetMask.description: The IP network mask of an entry of the static IP routing table.

dodRemoteIPNetHops.name: dodRemoteIPNetHops
dodRemoteIPNetHops.description: The hop count for the specified IP network address and destination name.

dodRemoteIPNetOperation.name: dodRemoteIPNetOperation
dodRemoteIPNetOperation.description: add -- add a static IP route to this destination. remove -- delete a static IP route to this destination. To access the other objects in this entry (mask, hops) the SNMP manager should add an entry first and then set those other objects.

dodRemoteIPNetGateway.name: dodRemoteIPNetGateway
dodRemoteIPNetGateway.description: The IP address of the gateway to which packets are sent when the static route is over a broadcast medium, such as when dodProtocol is RFC1483 with Mac Encapsulated Routing. When the medium is point-to-point, this field is ignored.

dodRemoteIPXNetTable.name: dodRemoteIPXNetTable
dodRemoteIPXNetTable.description: The static IPX routing table. It is based on indexes of destination name and IPX network number.

dodRemoteIPXNetAddress.name: dodRemoteIPXNetAddress
dodRemoteIPXNetAddress.description: The IPX network address of an entry of the static IPX routing table.

dodRemoteIPXNetMetric.name: dodRemoteIPXNetMetric
dodRemoteIPXNetMetric.description: The number of hops to reach this IPX network (via this destination).

dodRemoteIPXNetTicks.name: dodRemoteIPXNetTicks
dodRemoteIPXNetTicks.description: Number of 1/18th of seconds ticks necessary to reach this IPX network number (via this destination).

dodRemoteIPXNetOperation.name: dodRemoteIPXNetOperation
dodRemoteIPXNetOperation.description: add -- add a static IPX route to this destination remove -- delete a static IPX route for this destination For IPX metric and ticks, the SNMP manager should create the entry first and then set those attributes.

dodRemoteIPXNetStrAddress.name: dodRemoteIPXNetStrAddress
dodRemoteIPXNetStrAddress.description: The IPX network address of an entry of the static IPX routing table. This is an alternative to the dodRemoteIPXNetAddress object to be used when OCTET STRINGs are not implemented. In this case, specify the IPX network number as an ASCII string containing from 1 to 8 characters, to be converted to hexadecimal by the firmware.

dodRemoteIPXSAPTable.name: dodRemoteIPXSAPTable
dodRemoteIPXSAPTable.description: The remote IPX SAP table. It is based on indexes of DOD destination name, IPX network address, IPX node number, and IPX socket number.

dodRemoteIPXSAPIndex.name: dodRemoteIPXSAPIndex
dodRemoteIPXSAPIndex.description: Use dodRemoteIPXSAPNetAddress, dodRemoteIPXSAPNodeAddress dodRemoteIPXSAPSocket as indexes. Not used.

dodRemoteIPXSAPName.name: dodRemoteIPXSAPName
dodRemoteIPXSAPName.description: The name by which this IPX service is known.

dodRemoteIPXSAPNetAddress.name: dodRemoteIPXSAPNetAddress
dodRemoteIPXSAPNetAddress.description: The internal IPX network number of the server providing this particular IPX service.

dodRemoteIPXSAPNodeAddress.name: dodRemoteIPXSAPNodeAddress
dodRemoteIPXSAPNodeAddress.description: The node address on the IPX network number on which a server provides this particular IPX service.

dodRemoteIPXSAPSocket.name: dodRemoteIPXSAPSocket
dodRemoteIPXSAPSocket.description: The socket (i.e. internal port number) at which the specified IPX service is provided in the server.

dodRemoteIPXSAPType.name: dodRemoteIPXSAPType
dodRemoteIPXSAPType.description: The well-known type of service (i.e. File Service, Advertising Print Service, etc...)

dodRemoteIPXSAPHops.name: dodRemoteIPXSAPHops
dodRemoteIPXSAPHops.description: The number of hops necessary to reach the provider of this service.

dodRemoteIPXSAPOperation.name: dodRemoteIPXSAPOperation
dodRemoteIPXSAPOperation.description: add -- add a new IPX SAP service to this destination remove -- delete an IPX SAP service from this destination For the IPX network address, node address, socket number, type and hops, the SNMP manager should set those after creating the entry.

dodRemoteIPXSAPStrNetAddress.name: dodRemoteIPXSAPStrNetAddress
dodRemoteIPXSAPStrNetAddress.description: The internal IPX network number of the server providing this particular IPX service, expressed as an ASCII string, converted to hexadecimal by the firmware.

dodRemoteIPXSAPStrSocket.name: dodRemoteIPXSAPStrSocket
dodRemoteIPXSAPStrSocket.description: The socket (i.e. internal port number) at which the specified IPX service is provided in the server, expressed as an ASCII string, converted to hexadecimal by the firmware.

dodRemoteIPXSAPStrType.name: dodRemoteIPXSAPStrType
dodRemoteIPXSAPStrType.description: The well-known type of service (i.e. File Service, Advertising Print Service, etc...), expressed as an ASCII string, converted to hexadecimal by the firmware.

dodIPFilterTable.name: dodIPFilterTable
dodIPFilterTable.description: A set of IP filters defined for this remote.

dodIPXFilterTable.name: dodIPXFilterTable
dodIPXFilterTable.description: A set of IPX filters defined for this remote.

dodOperation.name: dodOperation
dodOperation.description: Use this object to give commands to save, load or erase DOD configuration in FLASH memory.

dodRemoteMacDefault.name: dodRemoteMacDefault
dodRemoteMacDefault.description: for GET : This object gives the remote destination name of default bridge. for SET : To set new default bridge, just give the the desired destination name. To delete and disable existing default bridge, just give a NULL string.

dodCallerTable.name: dodCallerTable
dodCallerTable.description: The Caller table: this is the list of numbers to search when receiving an incoming call, to identify the remote peer which made that call and thus find the corresponding dodEntry record. This table is used to implement dial-back and also to implement Caller ID verification (i.e. denying access to an unknown caller).

dodCallerEntry.name: dodCallerEntry
dodCallerEntry.description: Telephone numbers (or call information) of potential callers.

dodCallerNumber.name: dodCallerNumber
dodCallerNumber.description: The number against which caller ID verification takes place or used to find out which peer is calling before dial-back takes place.

dodCallerOperation.name: dodCallerOperation
dodCallerOperation.description: The operation being performed on a Caller data set: add or remove an entry for the specified remote and connection type.

dodIPTranslationServerTable.name: dodIPTranslationServerTable
dodIPTranslationServerTable.description: The IP Translation Server Table. Used to select a server when doing IP address translation.

dodIPTranslationServerIPAddress.name: dodIPTranslationServerIPAddress
dodIPTranslationServerIPAddress.description: The IP address of the Server when doing IP Address translation.

dodIPTranslationProtocol.name: dodIPTranslationProtocol
dodIPTranslationProtocol.description: The protocol used by this Server.

dodIPFirstTranslationPort.name: dodIPFirstTranslationPort
dodIPFirstTranslationPort.description: First public port in range used by this server. This port is what is referenced by the client. A port of 0 is a wild-card signifying any port.

dodIPLastTranslationPort.name: dodIPLastTranslationPort
dodIPLastTranslationPort.description: Last public port in range used by this server. This port is the last port in range and is referenced by the client.. This value must be greater than or equal first public port in range.

dodIPFirstPrivatePort.name: dodIPFirstPrivatePort
dodIPFirstPrivatePort.description: This is the first private port in range as seen by the server. The public port range is mapped to this private port range. If the public port range is to be the same as the private port range, this port should be the same as the first public port.

dodIPTranslationStatus.name: dodIPTranslationStatus
dodIPTranslationStatus.description: The status column used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the columnar objects in this table.

dodNatHostMappingTable.name: dodNatHostMappingTable
dodNatHostMappingTable.description: The NAT Host Mapping Table. Used to select a NAT Host Mapping when doing IP address translation.

dodFirstPrivateIPAddress.name: dodFirstPrivateIPAddress
dodFirstPrivateIPAddress.description: The first private IP address which starts the range of private IP addresses which are mapped to public IP addresses.

dodLastPrivateIPAddress.name: dodLastPrivateIPAddress
dodLastPrivateIPAddress.description: The last private IP address which ends the range of private IP addresses which are mapped to public IP addresses.

dodFirstPublicIPAddress.name: dodFirstPublicIPAddress
dodFirstPublicIPAddress.description: The first public IP address which starts the range of public IP Addresses which are mapped to private IP addresses. The last public IP address in the range is calculated by counting the number of private IP addresses in the private IP address range and creating an equivalent number of IP addresses in the public IP address range so there is a one to one mapping of public IP addresses to private IP addresses.

dodNatHostMappingStatus.name: dodNatHostMappingStatus
dodNatHostMappingStatus.description: The status column used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the columnar objects in this table.

fpEtherTable.name: fpEtherTable
fpEtherTable.description: The Ethernet interface configuration table for each port

fpPortNum.name: fpPortNum
fpPortNum.description: The identifier number of this interface port.

fpBridgeState.name: fpBridgeState
fpBridgeState.description: The object is used to show current state (enabled/ disabled) of the bridging the LAN port (ethernet). 1 -- the bridging is enabled. 2 -- the bridging is disabled. The bridging is enabled/disabled by controlling the dodRemoteMacState object of all the destinations. This field is only writeable on systems that don't support remote destinations (the DOD table).

fpIpState.name: fpIpState
fpIpState.description: Determines whether the IP protocol is routed (enable) or not (disable) via this LAN interface. A change requires rebooting. If the IP address and the network mask are defined and IP routing is not enabled, this system acts as an IP host only.

fpIpxState.name: fpIpxState
fpIpxState.description: Determines whether the IPX protocol is routed (enable) or not (disable) via this LAN interface. A change requires rebooting.

fpIpNetAddress.name: fpIpNetAddress
fpIpNetAddress.description: This object allows to get or set the IP address for this LAN interface: a change requires rebooting.

fpIpNetMask.name: fpIpNetMask
fpIpNetMask.description: This object allows to get or set the IP network mask for this LAN interface: a change requires rebooting.

fpIpxNetAddress.name: fpIpxNetAddress
fpIpxNetAddress.description: This objects allows to get or set the IPX external network number for this LAN port: a change requires rebooting.

fpIpxFrameType.name: fpIpxFrameType
fpIpxFrameType.description: This objects allows to get or set the IPX frame type generated by the router for this LAN port: a change requires rebooting. Possible values are: 802.2 (using the Novell SAP 0xE0), 802.3 (the IPX packet follows the Ethernet header immediately with no type) and Ethernet-II (named DIX) where the Ethertype is 0x8137.

fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP.name: fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP
fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP.description: Allows the processing of IP RIP 1 and RIP 2 packets received from for this LAN port: a change requires rebooting. This setting is enabled by default. fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP, fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP1, and fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP2 are mutually exclusive.

fpEtherIpOptSendRIP.name: fpEtherIpOptSendRIP
fpEtherIpOptSendRIP.description: Allows sending IP RIP 1 compatible packets to this LAN port when IP routing is enabled: a change requires rebooting. This setting is enabled by default. fpEtherIpOptSendRIP, fpEtherIpOptSendRIP1, and fpEtherIpOptSendRIP2 are mutually exclusive.

fpEtherIpOptRecvRIPDefault.name: fpEtherIpOptRecvRIPDefault
fpEtherIpOptRecvRIPDefault.description: Allows updating the IP routing table with the default route (i.e. 0.0.0.0) received from this LAN port when IP routing is enabled: this setting is enabled by default. A change on this object requires rebooting.

fpEtherIpOptSendRIPDefault.name: fpEtherIpOptSendRIPDefault
fpEtherIpOptSendRIPDefault.description: Allows this system to advertise itself as the default router on this LAN port when IP routing is enabled. This setting is enabled by default. A change requires rebooting.

fpIpxStrNetAddress.name: fpIpxStrNetAddress
fpIpxStrNetAddress.description: This objects allows to get or set the IPX external network number for this LAN port: a change requires rebooting. This object is expressed as an ASCII string, converted to hexadecimal by the firmware: use this object instead of fpIpxNetAddress when OCTET STRING is not implemented.

fpIpDefaultGateway.name: fpIpDefaultGateway
fpIpDefaultGateway.description: This object allows to get or set the IP address for the default Gateway (default route), and assign it to the interface specified by fpPortNum. This is particularly useful when the device operates as an end-system (host) as opposed to performing IP routing. There can be only one default route in the whole system. When set to 0.0.0.0, no default is defined statically, and it may be discovered dynamically if RIP is allowed on the LAN interface.

fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP1.name: fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP1
fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP1.description: Allows the processing of IP RIP 1 packets received from for this LAN port: a change requires rebooting. fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP, fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP1, and fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP2 are mutually exclusive.

fpEtherIpOptSendRIP1.name: fpEtherIpOptSendRIP1
fpEtherIpOptSendRIP1.description: Allows sending IP RIP 1 packets to this LAN port when IP routing is enabled: a change requires rebooting. fpEtherIpOptSendRIP, fpEtherIpOptSendRIP1, and fpEtherIpOptSendRIP2 are mutually exclusive.

fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP2.name: fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP2
fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP2.description: Allows the processing of IP RIP 2 packets received from for this LAN port: a change requires rebooting. fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP, fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP1, and fpEtherIpOptRecvRIP2 are mutually exclusive.

fpEtherIpOptSendRIP2.name: fpEtherIpOptSendRIP2
fpEtherIpOptSendRIP2.description: Allows sending IP RIP 2 packets to this LAN port when IP routing is enabled: a change requires rebooting. fpEtherIpOptSendRIP, fpEtherIpOptSendRIP1, and fpEtherIpOptSendRIP2 are mutually exclusive.

fpIpRIPMulticastAddress.name: fpIpRIPMulticastAddress
fpIpRIPMulticastAddress.description: This object allows to get or set the RIP 2 Multicast address for this LAN interface: set to 0.0.0.0 to restore the default multicast address (i.e. 224.0.0.9). A change requires rebooting.

fpNATState.name: fpNATState
fpNATState.description: Determines whether IP address/port translation is performed via this LAN interface if the IP protocol is routed (enable) through this LAN interface. A change requires rebooting.

fpMtu.name: fpMtu
fpMtu.description: When non-zero, the desired MTU size for this interface. When zero, use the default MTU size for the interface. The MTU size used is the minimum of the desired MTU size for this interface and the maximum MTU size allowed for the interface.

fpEtherOperation.name: fpEtherOperation
fpEtherOperation.description: This object is used to save/load/erase the LAN port (ethernet) configuration to/from FLASH.

etherNatHostMappingTable.name: etherNatHostMappingTable
etherNatHostMappingTable.description: The NAT Host Mapping Table. Used to select a NAT Host Mapping when doing IP address translation.

etherFirstPrivateIPAddress.name: etherFirstPrivateIPAddress
etherFirstPrivateIPAddress.description: The first private IP address which starts the range of private IP addresses which are mapped to public IP addresses.

etherLastPrivateIPAddress.name: etherLastPrivateIPAddress
etherLastPrivateIPAddress.description: The last private IP address which ends the range of private IP addresses which are mapped to public IP addresses.

etherFirstPublicIPAddress.name: etherFirstPublicIPAddress
etherFirstPublicIPAddress.description: The first public IP address which starts the range of public IP Addresses which are mapped to private IP addresses. The last public IP address in the range is calculated by counting the number of private IP addresses in the private IP address range and creating an equivalent number of IP addresses in the public IP address range so there is a one to one mapping of public IP addresses to private IP addresses.

etherNatHostMappingStatus.name: etherNatHostMappingStatus
etherNatHostMappingStatus.description: The status column used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the columnar objects in this table.

etherIPTranslationServerTable.name: etherIPTranslationServerTable
etherIPTranslationServerTable.description: The IP Translation Server Table. Used to select a server when doing IP address translation.

etherIPTranslationServerIPAddress.name: etherIPTranslationServerIPAddress
etherIPTranslationServerIPAddress.description: The IP address of the Server when doing IP Address translation.

etherIPTranslationProtocol.name: etherIPTranslationProtocol
etherIPTranslationProtocol.description: The protocol used by this Server.

etherIPFirstTranslationPort.name: etherIPFirstTranslationPort
etherIPFirstTranslationPort.description: First public port in range used by this server. This port is what is referenced by the client. A port of 0 is a wild-card signifying any port.

etherIPLastTranslationPort.name: etherIPLastTranslationPort
etherIPLastTranslationPort.description: Last public port in range used by this server. This port is the last port in range and is referenced by the client.. This value must be greater than or equal first public port in range.

etherIPFirstPrivatePort.name: etherIPFirstPrivatePort
etherIPFirstPrivatePort.description: This is the first private port in range as seen by the server. The public port range is mapped to this private port range. If the public port range is to be the same as the private port range, this port should be the same as the first public port.

etherIPTranslationStatus.name: etherIPTranslationStatus
etherIPTranslationStatus.description: The status column used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the columnar objects in this table.

fpIsdnCh1Spid.name: fpIsdnCh1Spid
fpIsdnCh1Spid.description: The spid number string for 1st B channel.

fpIsdnCh2Spid.name: fpIsdnCh2Spid
fpIsdnCh2Spid.description: The spid number string for 2nd B channel.

fpIsdnCh1DirectoryNum.name: fpIsdnCh1DirectoryNum
fpIsdnCh1DirectoryNum.description: The directory number string for 1st B channel.

fpIsdnCh2DirectoryNum.name: fpIsdnCh2DirectoryNum
fpIsdnCh2DirectoryNum.description: The directory number string for 2nd B channel.

fpIsdnOperation.name: fpIsdnOperation
fpIsdnOperation.description: To save or load or erase the ISDN configuration to/from FLASH memory.

fpIsdnCh1Status.name: fpIsdnCh1Status
fpIsdnCh1Status.description: This object shows the current status of B channel 1.

fpIsdnCh2Status.name: fpIsdnCh2Status
fpIsdnCh2Status.description: This object shows the current status of B channel 2.

fpIsdnCh1ClearCode.name: fpIsdnCh1ClearCode
fpIsdnCh1ClearCode.description: The clearing code of the last call, (0 if a call is in progress) for B channel 1.

fpIsdnCh2ClearCode.name: fpIsdnCh2ClearCode
fpIsdnCh2ClearCode.description: The clearing code of the last call, (0 if a call is in progress) for B channel 2.

fpIsdnCh1ClearReason.name: fpIsdnCh1ClearReason
fpIsdnCh1ClearReason.description: An explanation (in ASCII) of why the last called was cleared for B channel 1 (the null string if a call is in progress).

fpIsdnCh2ClearReason.name: fpIsdnCh2ClearReason
fpIsdnCh2ClearReason.description: An explanation (in ASCII) of why the last called was cleared for B channel 2 (the null string if a call is in progress).

fpIsdnSpeed.name: fpIsdnSpeed
fpIsdnSpeed.description: Whether the ISDN calls are made at a speed determined by the speed defined in the remote database and processed as indicated by the network (auto) or locked at 56Kb/s, regardless of the remote database settings and the parameters indicated by the network in incoming calls.

fpIsdnDataCallsIn.name: fpIsdnDataCallsIn
fpIsdnDataCallsIn.description: This object determines whether ISDN data calls can be received.

fpIsdnDataCallsOut.name: fpIsdnDataCallsOut
fpIsdnDataCallsOut.description: This object determines whether ISDN data calls can be generated by the device. This can be useful to let the device place voice calls only while ensuring that no data call is ever placed because the filtering/spoofing did not eliminate spurious traffic.

fpIsdnLineStatus.name: fpIsdnLineStatus
fpIsdnLineStatus.description: This object shows the current status of the line.

fpIsdnStatus.name: fpIsdnStatus
fpIsdnStatus.description: This object sets/returns the service state for the ISDN line.

fpIsdnAutoSpidCounter.name: fpIsdnAutoSpidCounter
fpIsdnAutoSpidCounter.description: The spid index currently being tried when doing auto spid detection.

fpIsdnSwitchTable.name: fpIsdnSwitchTable
fpIsdnSwitchTable.description: The switch table contains the switches supported by this kernel.

fpIsdnSwitchEntry.name: fpIsdnSwitchEntry
fpIsdnSwitchEntry.description: Each entry represents one switch type supported by this kernel.

fpSysName.name: fpSysName
fpSysName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this managed node. It will be the same name as the one defined in MIB2.

fpSysMessage.name: fpSysMessage
fpSysMessage.description: An administratively-assigned message for this managed node.

fpSysPassword.name: fpSysPassword
fpSysPassword.description: An administratively-assigned password for this managed node. The password will be used in the authentication phase of PPP. GENERR is returned if not authorized to read the fpSysPassword.

fpSysAuthen.name: fpSysAuthen
fpSysAuthen.description: An administratively-assigned authentication override type for this managed node. This is normally set to NONE, which means the normal rules apply. When set to PAP, all the remote entries that have a setting of PAP don't attempt to negotiate CHAP first, but propose only PAP. When set to CHAP, only CHAP authentication is accepted by this node (this makes it easier than changing all the remote entries to have their minimal level of authentication set to CHAP).

fpSysOperation.name: fpSysOperation
fpSysOperation.description: Use this object to save/load the system configuration (only what is defined in this group) to/from FLASH memory, or perform other control operation such as reboot.

fpSysSoftwareVer.name: fpSysSoftwareVer
fpSysSoftwareVer.description: Displays the software version run by the system.

fpSysHardwareVer.name: fpSysHardwareVer
fpSysHardwareVer.description: Displays the system model number, revision and serial number.

fpLoginPassword.name: fpLoginPassword
fpLoginPassword.description: Assign or change the administrator's password for login. Writing objects can only be performed when logged-in, using this password. To supply the password for login purposes, use the fpLoginTable object in the fplogin group. GENERR is returned if not authorized to read the fpLoginPassword.

fpWriteTimeout.name: fpWriteTimeout
fpWriteTimeout.description: To set and retrieve a timeout value (in minutes) during which a user logged in can modify objects. When setting this value, the countdown restarts. The timer is first started when the login password is supplied (see the LoginTable object). When the timer expires, a new login must be performed or all writes to writable objects return READONLY. Default -- 10 minutes (until changed). No security timeout -- set to 0.

fpWriteTimer.name: fpWriteTimer
fpWriteTimer.description: This object retrieves the current security timer value. It returns how many minutes are left (if any) before a new login must be performed.

fpCommunityName.name: fpCommunityName
fpCommunityName.description: To change or retrieve the SNMP community name. The default name is 'public'.

fpInternetFireWall.name: fpInternetFireWall
fpInternetFireWall.description: To enable or disable the internet firewall filter. The filter discards any IP packet arriving from the WAN with a source IP address belonging to the LAN.

fpSysLogout.name: fpSysLogout
fpSysLogout.description: Writing to this object prevents any change from any SNMP manager (until logged in again). Changes from telnet and the console are controlled via the login and logout commands, and are independent. After a reboot, SNMP managers are logged out and should log in before changing any configuration.

fpIpxSupported.name: fpIpxSupported
fpIpxSupported.description: Indicates whether or not IPX is supported in the router software. For compatibility with previous non-IPX-capable builds, the manager should consider that an error of NOSUCHNAME on this object means that IPX is NOT supported.

fpSysCallerIdTable.name: fpSysCallerIdTable
fpSysCallerIdTable.description: This table defines the types of connections for which CallerID information should be verified.

fpSysCallerIdEntry.name: fpSysCallerIdEntry
fpSysCallerIdEntry.description: An entry in the fpSysCallerIdTable specifies that calls of the type used as an index, should be validated by Caller ID verification (using dodCallerTable).

fpCallerIdEnabled.name: fpCallerIdEnabled
fpCallerIdEnabled.description: Set this object to enable or disable CallerId verification for the specified type of connection.

fpMIBCompatibility.name: fpMIBCompatibility
fpMIBCompatibility.description: Indicates that this private MIB is fully compatible with RFC 1155. For compatibility with previous builds, the manager should consider that an error of NOSUCHNAME on this object means that the 'old' value applies, (meaning the enumeration of INTEGERs are mostly zero-based instead of one-based).

fpPOTSInstalled.name: fpPOTSInstalled
fpPOTSInstalled.description: Indicates whether or not POTS hardware is installed AND is software supported. For compatibility with previous builds, the manager should consider that an error of NOSUCHNAME on this object means that POTS hardware and software are not available.

fpSysLastLogEvent.name: fpSysLastLogEvent
fpSysLastLogEvent.description: The last system event reported to the console. This includes the timestamp, the subsystem and the actual text message of the event.

fpSysSingleUser.name: fpSysSingleUser
fpSysSingleUser.description: This IP address used to define the single address to which IP translation was to occur (one client system at a time), or cancelling the translation when NULL. Network Address Translation (NAT) and its ability to define server mappings (with sysIPTranslationServerTable) has rendered this object obsolete: this object is now always returned as the IP address 0.0.0.0 and cannot be set to anything else.

fpSysYear.name: fpSysYear
fpSysYear.description: Set this object to specify the year for the real time clock, protected by a battery when the power is off. When all the related parameters (fpSysYear, fpSysMonth, fpSysDay, fpSysHour, fpSysMinute, fpSysSecond) are set, set the fpSysOperation to set-clock(5).

fpSysMonth.name: fpSysMonth
fpSysMonth.description: Set this object to specify the month for the real time clock, protected by a battery when the power is off. When all the related parameters (fpSysYear, fpSysMonth, fpSysDay, fpSysHour, fpSysMinute, fpSysSecond) are set, set the fpSysOperation to set-clock(5).

fpSysDay.name: fpSysDay
fpSysDay.description: Set this object to specify the day for the real time clock, protected by a battery when the power is off. When all the related parameters (fpSysYear, fpSysMonth, fpSysDay, fpSysHour, fpSysMinute, fpSysSecond) are set, set the fpSysOperation to set-clock(5).

fpSysHour.name: fpSysHour
fpSysHour.description: Set this object to specify the hour for the real time clock, protected by a battery when the power is off. When all the related parameters (fpSysYear, fpSysMonth, fpSysDay, fpSysHour, fpSysMinute, fpSysSecond) are set, set the fpSysOperation to set-clock(5).

fpSysMinute.name: fpSysMinute
fpSysMinute.description: Set this object to specify the minutes for the real time clock, protected by a battery when the power is off. When all the related parameters (fpSysYear, fpSysMonth, fpSysDay, fpSysHour, fpSysMinute, fpSysSecond) are set, set the fpSysOperation to set-clock(5).

fpSysSecond.name: fpSysSecond
fpSysSecond.description: Set this object to specify the seconds for the real time clock, protected by a battery when the power is off. When all the related parameters (fpSysYear, fpSysMonth, fpSysDay, fpSysHour, fpSysMinute, fpSysSecond) are set, set the fpSysOperation to set-clock(5).

fpSysDefaultSingleUser.name: fpSysDefaultSingleUser
fpSysDefaultSingleUser.description: Network Address Translation (NAT) and its ability to define server mappings (with sysIPTranslationServerTable) has rendered this object obsolete. For backwards compatibility purposes, this object still allows to set the IP address of the client for which IP address translation is to be performed by default. However, to take effect, the configuration must be saved (with fpEtherOperation=save(1)) and the system must be restarted.

fpSysBootpRelay.name: fpSysBootpRelay
fpSysBootpRelay.description: This object allows to get or set the IP address of the DHCP/BOOTP Server when this router is acting as a Bootp relay agent. When set to 0.0.0.0, this router will not act as a Bootp relay agent. This setting is saved to non-volatile memory, with both fpSysOperation=save(1) and fpEtherOperation=save(1).

fpSysKernelRevision.name: fpSysKernelRevision
fpSysKernelRevision.description: This object represents the number of times that the source code got changed, possibly resulting in the support of new features. This number is intended to be used by an SNMP manager to determine what features set is supported by the kernel software (compared to what is expected as a minimum). This objects differs from fpSysSoftwareVer which is a string containing an administratively defined version.

fpSysTelnetPort.name: fpSysTelnetPort
fpSysTelnetPort.description: The TCP port for reception of telnet connections to the router. Setting this value to zero disables telnetting to the router. This change requires a reboot to take affect.

fpSysSNMPPort.name: fpSysSNMPPort
fpSysSNMPPort.description: The TCP port for reception of SNMP requests to the router. Setting this value to zero disables SNMP management of the router. This change requires a reboot to take affect.

fpWAN2WANForwarding.name: fpWAN2WANForwarding
fpWAN2WANForwarding.description: To enable or disable the forwarding of data traffic from one wan link to another wan link.

fpUdpRelayTable.name: fpUdpRelayTable
fpUdpRelayTable.description: This table defines UDP ports for which relaying should should be performed when this UDP traffic is broadcast.

fpUdpRelayEntry.name: fpUdpRelayEntry
fpUdpRelayEntry.description: An entry in the fpUdpRelayTable specifies that UDP packets which are broadcast to the specified ports should be relayed to the specified IP address.

fpUdpRelayFirstPort.name: fpUdpRelayFirstPort
fpUdpRelayFirstPort.description: First UDP port of range of UDP ports which will be relayed.

fpUdpRelayLastPort.name: fpUdpRelayLastPort
fpUdpRelayLastPort.description: Last UDP port of range of UDP ports which will be relayed.

fpUdpRelayIPAddress.name: fpUdpRelayIPAddress
fpUdpRelayIPAddress.description: IP address to receive UDP broadcast traffic.

fpUdpRelayStatus.name: fpUdpRelayStatus
fpUdpRelayStatus.description: The status column used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the columnar objects in this table.

fpOneWANConnection.name: fpOneWANConnection
fpOneWANConnection.description: To enable or disable the bringing up of more than one wan link at a time to different destinations.

fpSysHTTPPort.name: fpSysHTTPPort
fpSysHTTPPort.description: The TCP port for reception of HTTP requests to the router. Setting this value to zero disables HTTP management of the router. This change requires a reboot to take affect.

fpDirectedBroadcasts.name: fpDirectedBroadcasts
fpDirectedBroadcasts.description: Enable/disable directed broadcasts to a directly connected interface.

fpBlockNetBIOSDefault.name: fpBlockNetBIOSDefault
fpBlockNetBIOSDefault.description: To set the default when a new remote is created that controls if the remote will block NetBIOS traffic.

fpSysFlashAvailable.name: fpSysFlashAvailable
fpSysFlashAvailable.description: This object represents the number of bytes of flash available in the flash file system.

fpVoiceTable.name: fpVoiceTable
fpVoiceTable.description: This table defines voice ports for voice routers.

fpVoiceEntry.name: fpVoiceEntry
fpVoiceEntry.description: An entry in the fpVoiceTable specifies voice information for an voice router; such as the ATM PVC or the Frame Relay DLCI.

fpVoicePort.name: fpVoicePort
fpVoicePort.description: This object represents the ATM PVC or the Frame Relay DLCI number for the voice port.

fpEchoEntry.name: fpEchoEntry
fpEchoEntry.description: An entry in the fpEchoTable specifies echo information for a voice router; such as the ATM PVC or the Frame Relay DLCI.

fpEchoPort.name: fpEchoPort
fpEchoPort.description: This object represents the ATM PVC or the Frame Relay DLCI number for the echo port.

fpOptionEntry.name: fpOptionEntry
fpOptionEntry.description: A string in the fpOptionTable specifies information pertaining to options built into the kernel -and- which options are available.

fpOptionIndex.name: fpOptionIndex
fpOptionIndex.description: An index number representing a line of options.

fpOptionString.name: fpOptionString
fpOptionString.description: This object represents a an string for the option built into the kernel.

fpOptionAvailable.name: fpOptionAvailable
fpOptionAvailable.description: Returns enable(1) if the option is available for use.

fpLoginTable.name: fpLoginTable
fpLoginTable.description: This object returns the login status to the Manager.

fpLoginAction.name: fpLoginAction
fpLoginAction.description: This object will return the login status to the Manager. Use this object to login to system by giving the administrator's password as index. The login status are: 1 -- login OK. Password matches with system's password. 2 -- login fail. Password mismatch.

fpWanTable.name: fpWanTable
fpWanTable.description: A list of WAN interface entries.

fpWanEntry.name: fpWanEntry
fpWanEntry.description: An interface entry containing objects at the WAN layer...

fpWanInstantOutUtil.name: fpWanInstantOutUtil
fpWanInstantOutUtil.description: Intantaneous output bandwidth utilization, from 0 to 100 (in 1% increments).

fpWanInstantInUtil.name: fpWanInstantInUtil
fpWanInstantInUtil.description: Intantaneous input bandwidth utilization, from 0 to 100 (in 1% increments).

fpWanAvgOutUtil.name: fpWanAvgOutUtil
fpWanAvgOutUtil.description: Sliding average of output bandwidth utilization, from 0 to 100 (in 1% increments).

fpWanAvgInUtil.name: fpWanAvgInUtil
fpWanAvgInUtil.description: Sliding average of input bandwidth utilization, from 0 to 100 (in 1% increments).

fpWanRemoteName.name: fpWanRemoteName
fpWanRemoteName.description: Name of user/destination that this port is currently connected to, if known.

fpWanRemoteTime.name: fpWanRemoteTime
fpWanRemoteTime.description: The number of seconds that we have been connected to this particular remote across this WAN link.

fpWanIfIndex.name: fpWanIfIndex
fpWanIfIndex.description: The corresponding MIB-II ifIndex for this interface

fpWanOutSpeed.name: fpWanOutSpeed
fpWanOutSpeed.description: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in bits per second, for the transmit side (relative to this device).

fpWanInSpeed.name: fpWanInSpeed
fpWanInSpeed.description: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in bits per second, for the receive side (relative to this device).

potsOperation.name: potsOperation
potsOperation.description: Use this object to give commands to save, load or erase POTS configuration in FLASH memory.

potsTable.name: potsTable
potsTable.description: The table used to configure and manage the POTS interfaces.

potsIndex.name: potsIndex
potsIndex.description: Index used to access a potsEntry: maps to the connectors marked POTS1 and POTS2.

potsEnabled.name: potsEnabled
potsEnabled.description: Enable or disable the POTS functionality at the specified connector.

potsOpMode.name: potsOpMode
potsOpMode.description: Specifies the type of calls that should be handled by this POTS interface. The default is to allow both incoming and outgoing calls.

potsPreemptMode.name: potsPreemptMode
potsPreemptMode.description: Specifies the behavior of analog calls versus data calls. The default is both: voice calls always preempt data calls.

potsAutoMode.name: potsAutoMode
potsAutoMode.description: Defines whether the preemption mode defined by potsPreemptMode is to be performed automatically or whether the user should be prompted first. This only applies when the preemption of that type is allowed.

potsPhoneCnt.name: potsPhoneCnt
potsPhoneCnt.description: Indicates the number of phone numbers associated with this POTS interface.

potsLocalNumber.name: potsLocalNumber
potsLocalNumber.description: The local phone number used by this POTS interface during the last analog call processed (incoming and outgoing).

potsRemoteNumber.name: potsRemoteNumber
potsRemoteNumber.description: The remote phone number used by this POTS interface during the last analog call processed (outgoing and incoming when caller ID is available).

potsState.name: potsState
potsState.description: Current state of this POTS interface.

potsIsdnChannel.name: potsIsdnChannel
potsIsdnChannel.description: Indicates which ISDN channel (1 or 2) is associated with this POTS interface for the duration of this call. Additional information (like the clearing cause and reason are available via the ISDN group variables. When no ISDN channel is assigned to this POTS interface yet, 0 is returned

potsWanIndex.name: potsWanIndex
potsWanIndex.description: Indicates which Wan interface (1 or 2) is associated with this POTS interface for the duration of this call. Additional information (like the duration of the call is available via the WAN interface group variables. When no WAN interface is mapped to this POTS interface yet, 0 is returned

potsPhoneTable.name: potsPhoneTable
potsPhoneTable.description: The table used to associate phone numbers and POTS interfaces.

potsPhoneNumber.name: potsPhoneNumber
potsPhoneNumber.description: A phone number associated with the specified POTS interface, such that when an incoming analog call arrives, that interface rings, if allowed. This is used as an index into the POTS phone number table.

potsPhoneOperation.name: potsPhoneOperation
potsPhoneOperation.description: Perform a set on this object to add or remove the association between the specified phone number and the specified POTS interface.

fpDLForceOnBoot.name: fpDLForceOnBoot
fpDLForceOnBoot.description: When set to a 1, the system will request a download, during the next system restart. If no server is found and the current image in flash memory is valid, the system will boot using the flash-resident image.

fpDLCommitRAMToFlash.name: fpDLCommitRAMToFlash
fpDLCommitRAMToFlash.description: This object only exists for compatibility reasons.

fpDLInitiateColdBoot.name: fpDLInitiateColdBoot
fpDLInitiateColdBoot.description: When written with a 1, the boot software intiates a system reboot. All MIB variables used to control the exact nature of the download should be set, prior to activating a system reset. A read always returns a 0.

fpDLTFTPRequestHost.name: fpDLTFTPRequestHost
fpDLTFTPRequestHost.description: The IP address of the server to be used, when firmware is to be loaded across the network (network boot).

fpDLTFTPRequest.name: fpDLTFTPRequest
fpDLTFTPRequest.description: The filename requested of the server, when firmware is to be loaded across the network (network boot).

fpDLLastImageFilename.name: fpDLLastImageFilename
fpDLLastImageFilename.description: Filename of the last image to be successfully loaded into memory.

fpDLLastServerIPAddress.name: fpDLLastServerIPAddress
fpDLLastServerIPAddress.description: The IP address of the server used to load the present image in flash memory.

fpDLFlashSize.name: fpDLFlashSize
fpDLFlashSize.description: Denotes the size, in bytes, of flash memory con- tained on this module.

fpDLFlashCount.name: fpDLFlashCount
fpDLFlashCount.description: Denotes the number of times that flash memory has been reprogrammed. This value is initialized to 1, when the module is initially powered up.

fpDLFirmwareBase.name: fpDLFirmwareBase
fpDLFirmwareBase.description: Denotes the starting address of the firmware in RAM.

fpDLFirmwareTop.name: fpDLFirmwareTop
fpDLFirmwareTop.description: Denotes the ending address of firmware in RAM.

fpDLFirmwareStart.name: fpDLFirmwareStart
fpDLFirmwareStart.description: Denotes the start address of the firmware, in RAM, as established by the boot process.

fpDLBootRev.name: fpDLBootRev
fpDLBootRev.description: Denotes the revision of boot firmware in the module. The first octets provides the version, and the second provides the revision.

fpDLForceBootp.name: fpDLForceBootp
fpDLForceBootp.description: When set, this variable forces the client to send a BOOTP request packet when rebooting. The client will make several attempts before timing out if a server does not respond. This variable stays set. When set to a 1 it should always be read as a one. When set to zero it should always be read as zero.

fpDLServerName.name: fpDLServerName
fpDLServerName.description: This OID is reserved for future use of the Bootp server name. This field can be used when a client wants to get boot information from a particular bootp server.

fpDLOnLineDownLoad.name: fpDLOnLineDownLoad
fpDLOnLineDownLoad.description: During normal operation this object has the value of 1. By setting this object to a value of forceDownLoad(2) an online download will be performed. By setting this object to a value of forceDownLoadReset(3) an online download will be performed and a reset will be forced upon successful completion of the download. The forceUpLoad(4) operation causes the local file specified in fpDLLocalFileName to be uploaded to the TFTP server fpDLNetAddress with the file name fpDLFileName. The forceRemove(5) operation deletes the local file specified in fpDLLocalFileName.

fpDLOperStatus.name: fpDLOperStatus
fpDLOperStatus.description: This object reflects the status of download/upload operations. A value of normalOperation(3) reflects either a download was started but has finished normally and no reset was specified or no download has been started. A value of downLoadActive only appears while a download is in progress. A value of downLoadCompleteError reflects that a download was started however an error was detected. Similarly when an upload is in progress upLoadActive(6) is returned and if an error occurs upLoadCompeteError(7) is returned. A value of removeActive(8) indicates that a local file is being removed and removeCompleteError(9) indicates a failure to remove the file.

fpDLNetAddress.name: fpDLNetAddress
fpDLNetAddress.description: IP Address of the server to be used when an image is to be downloaded using the Runtime TFTP Download.

fpDLFileName.name: fpDLFileName
fpDLFileName.description: Filename requested of the server when an image is to be downloaded using the Runtime TFTP Download. This should be a complete path filename.

fpDLErrorString.name: fpDLErrorString
fpDLErrorString.description: If the value of fpDLOperStatus is downloadCompleteError(5) or uploadCompleteError(7) then this object will provide a more complete description of the error. Otherwise this object will be the zero length string.

fpDLTftpServerGatewayIPAddress.name: fpDLTftpServerGatewayIPAddress
fpDLTftpServerGatewayIPAddress.description: The IP address of the gateway/router which connects this SNMP agent to the TFTP server (0.0.0.0 if none).

fpDLBlockCount.name: fpDLBlockCount
fpDLBlockCount.description: Current TFTP block count of an active session. If no TFTP transfer is in progress, zero is returned.

fpDLBootPartitionStatus.name: fpDLBootPartitionStatus
fpDLBootPartitionStatus.description: Status of the boot partition or paritions. A value of good(1) indicates that all boot partitions contain a valid checksum. A value of bad(2) indicates that one or more boot partitions contain an invalid checksum and the the image was not able to fix the invalid boot partition. A value of inProgress(3) indicates that the image is attempting to fix an invalid boot partition and this status will change to either good(1) or bad(2).

fpDLLocalFileName.name: fpDLLocalFileName
fpDLLocalFileName.description: Filename used on the local file system whenever a TFTP download or upload is to be processed.

fpDLBootVersion.name: fpDLBootVersion
fpDLBootVersion.description: Returns a string indicating the boot code version.

sysIPTranslationServerTable.name: sysIPTranslationServerTable
